1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,450
I spent a very interesting evening recently with a friend who is the president of a young but rapidly growing manufacturing concern.

2
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:13,569
The TV set happened to be turned to one of the most popular quiz programs.

3
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:17,329
The fellow being quizzed had been on the show for several weeks.

4
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:23,089
He could answer questions on all sorts of subjects, many of which seemed nonsensical.

5
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:29,569
After the fellow answered a particularly odd question, something about a mountain in Argentina,

6
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:35,490
my host looked at me and said, How much do you think I'd pay that guy to work for me?

7
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:37,410
How much, I asked.

8
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:43,970
Not a cent over three hundred dollars, not per week, not per month, but for life.

9
00:00:44,079 --> 00:00:45,650
I've sized him up.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,129
That expert can't think.

11
00:00:48,319 --> 00:00:49,889
He can only memorize.

12
00:00:50,079 --> 00:00:52,530
He's just a human encyclopedia.

13
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:57,730
And I figure for $300 I can buy a pretty good set of encyclopedias.

14
00:00:57,920 --> 00:01:00,210
In fact, maybe that's too much.

15
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:05,490
90% of what that guy knows I can find in a $2 almanac.

16
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:12,690
What I want around me, he continued, are people who can solve problems, who can think up ideas.

17
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:17,569
People who can dream and then develop the dream into a practical application.

18
00:01:17,839 --> 00:01:20,369
An idea man can make money with me.

19
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:22,290
A fact man can't.

